This paper deals with secure transmission and beamforming, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of limited feedback and optimization of transmission parameters also suggests a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed adaptive transmission strategy involves power allocation and channel quantization, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
